'''OpenAL''' (Open Audio Library) is a cross-platform audio application programming interface (API). It is designed for efficient rendering of multichannel three-dimensional positional audio. Its API style and conventions deliberately resemble those of OpenGL. ZDoom can use its free software implementation, '''OpenAL Soft''', with [http://www.mega-nerd.com/libsndfile/ libsndfile] and [//mpg123.org libmpg123] as file decoding backends.
